  "prompt": "What is the validity period of Non-Creamy OBC certificate?",
  "response": "The validity period of a Non-Creamy OBC (Other Backward Class) certificate can vary based on the regulations established by different state governments or organizations in India. Generally, a Non-Creamy OBC certificate is considered valid for a specific time frame, often ranging from one to three years. However, some institutions or departments may have their own guidelines regarding the renewal or reissuance of the certificate.\n\nIt's essential to check the specific requirements of the institution or organization for which you are applying, as they may have updated rules regarding the validity of the OBC certificate. Additionally, it is advisable to renew or obtain a new certificate if your existing one is nearing its expiry to avoid any issues during the application process.",
